<TEXT>
searchers found a missing man in the desert 
monday hours after he bolted in a fit from a helicopter taking him 
to his elderly father whod been lost in remote foothills for four 
days officials said 
joel behrends had been riding a kpnxtv helicopter sunday night 
to a reunion with his father who had been missing since thursday 
when he became agitated and insisted on being let out of the 
aircraft officials said 
he looked really uncomfortable he looked like he was going to 
have a claustrophobic fit said reporter marlene galan who was 
aboard the aircraft there wasnt any talking to him he wasnt 
going to reason with anyone i was afraid he was going to become 
violent 
the skids touched down his seat belt came off and he flew 
out the door said kpnxtv acting news director al macias he 
was seen taking off his shirt and running in the desert and was 
yelling incoherently 
the pilot took off and tried to spot behrends but was 
unsuccessful 
three helicopters 30 searchers and eight tracking dogs 
including six which tracked the elder behrends took part in the 
search for his son murphy said 
behrends 31 lit a signal fire which was spotted around 930 
am said yavapai county sheriffs capt bill murphy 
about 1 hours later an army national guard helicopter 
airlifted behrends out of the cellar basin area about 70 miles 
north of phoenix murphy said 
the young man indicated to one of our officers that he had 
been helping to trying to find his dad for three to four days had 
been out in the sun and was all stressedup and i guess when he 
got in that helicopter he just couldnt take it murphy said 
behrends 76yearold father william behrends of lamberton 
minn was rescued sunday 
the search for the father was much larger covering 17500 
square miles in yavapai pinal maricopa and gila counties 
authorities said 
gem hunter bob woods of phoenix found the elder behrends 
sleeping in his pickup truck sunday near wagoner about 50 miles 
northwest of phoenix officials said 
william behrends who was visiting relatives in phoenix left 
the city thursday after telling his wife he was going to photograph 
desert wildflowers his truck got stuck in the sand after he made a 
wrong turn murphy said 
on friday he walked nine miles to an isolated ranch but was 
afraid to enter because of dogs in the yard and a notrespassing 
sign officials said behrends turned around and walked the nine 
miles back to his truck 
the next day behrends walked to the ranch again but no one was 
home he drank from a stream and walked back to the truck 
william behrends who was tired and dehydrated when found was 
in fair condition monday at yavapai regional medical center in 
prescott 
</TEXT>
