<TEXT>
in a costcutting move defense minister valerio 
zanone has decided to cancel the annual military parade on italys 
constitution day 
zanone said he believed a ceremony at the recently reopened 
altar of the nation which is also known as the victor emmanuel 
monument would be a more appropriate way to mark the june 4 
holiday 
he said saturday that the decision was prompted by the need to 
cut spending in anticipation of cuts in the defense budget the 
government is trying to cut spending to deal with a projected 1989 
budget deficit of 896 billion 
instead of a military parade this years holiday will be marked 
by wreath placing ceremony at the altar of the nation by president 
francesco cossiga historical and military exhibits and band 
concerts 
</TEXT>
