of maoist shining path guerrillas for six hours near uchiza 245 
miles northeast of lima 
the fighting left 20 rebels dead and three soldiers wounded 
according to a military communique transmitted by andina 
the violence came two weeks after a column of rebels and drug 
traffickers overran the towns police post killing 10 policemen 
and three civilians 
uchiza is in the upper huallaga river valley a region known as 
perus cocaine cradle it has become a virtual nomans land 
overrun by drug traffickers and leftist guerrillas who protect them 
in exchange for money to purchase arms 
fourteen more rebels were slain when navy marines patrolling the 
ucayali river 180 miles south of uchiza battled a guerrilla 
column for several hours andina said 
the government did not indicate any troop casualties in that 
clash 
the centerleft government of president alan garcia has come 
under intense criticism since the uchiza attack for failing to 
adequately defend the post and to send reinforcements 
critics have renewed charges that the government has mismanaged 
the antiinsurgency effort allowing rebel violence to spread 
the shining path insurgency has claimed more than 14000 lives 
including guerrillas soldiers police and innocent peasants 
the fighting began in 1980 in the central andes mountains and 
has branched out to coastal urban centers and the eastern jungle 
