study had been criticized by one outside researcher as utilizing 
procedures that were bound to be biased in the navys favor 
nonetheless the study suggests a 37 percent difference between 
cancer rates for the general population and sailors aboard nuclear 
missile submarines 
the publication said the statistical tabulation reported an 
observed rate of cancer cases among missile submarine personnel 
of 54 compared to an expected rate for the general population 
of 394 
