shippingport pa is on the last leg of an 8000mile voyage to 
burial at the hanford wash nuclear reservation the us 
department of energy said radioactive fuel has been removed from 
the shell and it poses no threat to public health 
the barge passed into the colombia river near astoria monday 
morning and was expected to complete the 100mile journey to 
portland after dark said lt commander david gault of the coast 
guard 
near astoria the tug that brought the barge from pennsylvania 
through the panama canal turned back and was replaced by a tug 
