<TEXT>
stage fright that mysterious malady that 
renders a performer helpless in the footlights has been known to 
wreck many a budding career 
but in the case of the british rock band xtc whose new record 
oranges and lemons is climbing the charts it may actually have 
helped 
xtc was a struggling punk band in 1982 when leader andy 
partridge finding it more and more difficult to perform live 
collapsed on stage during a concert in paris it was his last live 
performance but instead of falling apart xtc became studio 
hermits and their music flowered 
rather than being a monotone creation something red and blue 
suddenly there were all these colors coming out in the music that 
we hadnt even considered putting in there partridge said in a 
telephone interview from his home in the english town of swindon 
from the 1982 album english settlement onward our music 
started getting a lot better he said but it wouldnt have 
done that if we hadnt gone off the road if we hadnt stopped 
touring i think in the space of a year the group would have split 
up 
xtcs music is like a lost letter from the 1960s a reflection 
of the british psychedelic beat groups with which partridge and 
partners colin moulding and dave gregory grew up their innate 
tunefulness is wedded to clever and occasionally provocative lyrics 
and though partridge is reluctant to publicly admit it the 
15song oranges and lemons is the peak of a recording career 
that began in 1978 the public thinks so the record is at no 47 
on the billboard charts led by the single the mayor of 
simpleton 
the breezy love song is a far cry from the groups last flirt 
with public attention in the united states the controversial 
single dear god drew protests in 1986 from fundamentalist 
groups angered by the implicit endorsement of atheism 
if people got upset by it they deserved to get upset by it 
partridge said its the truth 
actually the 35yearold musician said hes amused to attract 
so much notoriety for a song he considered a failure dear god 
was initially left off the album skylarking and released only 
as a bside to a single 
nothing on oranges and lemons is quite so explosive the 
mayor of simpleton attracts notice for the right reasons its a 
sprightly melody with lyrics about a man who knows he cant impress 
a woman with brains so he does it with love 
partridge said he took from his own experience of being labeled 
a failure for quitting school at age 15 
in england you tend to get written off as nothing as a piece 
of air if you left school and have no qualifications to do 
anything he said i felt like i didnt need those things i 
felt my emotions were intact and i knew enough to get by i felt 
like i had kind of innate intelligence that didnt need to be put 
in certificate form 
the mayor of simpleton is a love song that proves you 
dont need those certificates to be able to feel emotionally he 
said 
xtcs early music through songs such as making plans for 
nigel and generals and majors was known for its jerky 
rhythms and hyperactive pace constant touring had something to do 
with it partridge described the life as living on constant fear 
pellets 
i started to get stage fright which was rather ludicrous 
he said because rather than getting more relaxed on stage i was 
getting less relaxed more wound up 
leaving the road allowed xtc to experiment with new instruments 
and sounds without the worry of having to reproduce the music on 
stage it allowed such influences as the beatles and hollies to 
show 
xtc acknowledged these debts with a spinoff band called the 
dukes of stratosphear in two records the dukes eerily reproduced 
the sound of their favorite 60s bands particularly their 
psychedelic sides partridge said it was a musical thank you note 
ive always liked forgery he said i thought forgery was 
a fine art i used to forge money when i was a kid id sit for 
hours with different colored pens trying to get it right 
partridge writes roughly 80 percent of the groups music with 
moulding contributing a few songs per album the trio handles 
guitars and keyboards and hires a new drummer for each album 
project since the groups original drummer terry chambers left 
when the touring stopped mr mister drummer pat mastelotto handled 
the sticks for the new record 
partridge is the father of two children ages 3 and 1 and their 
influence can also be seen in oranges and lemons garden of 
earthly delights introduces a child to the wonders of the world 
and hold me my daddy is about coming to terms with love for a 
father 
they have not crept into the music partridge said of his 
children theyve more sort of crawled and crashed in at five in 
the morning i think its been very positive they have been an 
inspiration 
executives at geffen xtcs label initially tried to coax xtc 
back on stage but with the success of skylarking and oranges 
and lemons partridge said thats stopped since theyre selling 
more records than they ever did while touring why argue with 
success even if it contradicts standard industry practice 
partridge wont be spending his free time with the dukes who he 
said were killed in a bizarre cooking accident xtc is instead 
thinking of recording a sampler album in which they imitate a 
variety of bands and styles from the 1940s to the 1980s he said 
he chuckles at the thought that xtc which pays such a heavy 
debt to its own influences is now influencing another generation 
of music fans 
it makes me feel like theres some kind of potent chemical 
getting into their system he said 
