<TEXT>
the two top executives of cineplex odeon corp 
the major us and canadian theater operator and movie production 
house will effectively take control of the torontobased company 
under a stock purchase announced monday 
charles bronfman cochairman of the seagram co ltd sold his 
73 million shares in the company to a group led by cineplex 
chairman garth drabinsky officials announced 
it was good timing for us drabinsky said of the 1271 
million stock deal the price was attractive enough to entice the 
bronfmans and at the same time a price we could finance 
under the terms of the purchase drabinsky and vice chairman 
myron gottlieb will end up with effective control of cineplex for 
at least two years 
the group of 11 buyers including drabinsky and gottlieb paid 
1750 a share for the block of common shares which represents 29 
percent of those outstanding 
the deal closes may 3 and is subject to regulatory approval 
although drabinsky and gottlieb will only own a small portion of 
the stock an agreement with the nine other buyers lasting until 
april 30 1991 allows them to vote the shares as they please 
when that block is combined with personal holdings the pair 
controls 38 percent of the common shares 
mca inc the us media company owns 48 percent of cineplexs 
shares through an issue of restrictedvoting stock 
while drabinsky saw the move as good news investors didnt see 
it that way 
cineplex shares tumbled in early trading on the toronto stock 
exchange dropping 63 cents to 16 shortly after the announcement 
they recovered to close at 1625 off 38 cents on the day 
